significant BP change during the study.
CONCLUSION: In ESRD patients under long-term haemodialysis in whom BP was 
markedly elevated despite administration of many antihypertensive drugs, renal 
denervation lowered both ambulatory and office BP. The reduction persisted over 
a 1-year follow-up.

